WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.637 --> 00:00:15.558
Architecture is amazing, for sure.
毫无疑问，建筑学是很令人惊叹的。

2
00:00:17.177 --> 00:00:19.581
It's amazing because it's art.
其原因在于，它是一门艺术。

3
00:00:20.479 --> 00:00:22.857
But you know, it's a very funny kind of art.
不过这是一类非常有趣的艺术，

4
00:00:22.881 --> 00:00:26.757
It's an art at the frontier between art and science.
交织了艺术和科学的前沿艺术。

5
00:00:27.413 --> 00:00:29.329
It's fed by ...
它源自于…

6
00:00:30.873 --> 00:00:32.835
by real life, every day.
真实的常日生活。

7
00:00:33.451 --> 00:00:36.196
It's driven by force of necessity.
它受到了必要性的驱使。

8
00:00:37.133 --> 00:00:39.657
Quite amazing, quite amazing.
非常，非常惊艳。

9
00:00:39.681 --> 00:00:43.300
And the life of the architect is also amazing.
建筑师的生活一样很精彩。

10
00:00:44.868 --> 00:00:47.995
You know, as an architect, at 10 o’clock in the morning,
要知道，作为一个建筑师， 早上十点的时候，

11
00:00:48.019 --> 00:00:51.129
you need to be a poet, for sure.
你得当一个诗人。

12
00:00:51.153 --> 00:00:53.561
But at 11,
但是十一点的时候，

13
00:00:53.585 --> 00:00:56.191
you must become a humanist,
你又必须充满人文情怀，

14
00:00:56.215 --> 00:00:58.571
otherwise you'd lose your direction.
否则你会变得迷茫。

15
00:00:59.612 --> 00:01:04.030
And at noon, you absolutely need to be a builder.
但是下午的时候， 你又要做一个建筑工人。

16
00:01:04.756 --> 00:01:08.287
You need to be able to make a building,
你需要能够建造楼房。

17
00:01:08.311 --> 00:01:13.202
because architecture, at the end, is the art of making buildings.
因为建筑学，归根结底 是建筑的艺术。

18
00:01:13.730 --> 00:01:18.307
Architecture is the art of making shelter for human beings.
建筑学是为人们建造庇护所的艺术。

19
00:01:18.830 --> 00:01:20.348
Period.
目标明确。

20
00:01:20.698 --> 00:01:22.565
And this is not easy at all.
这一点也不容易实现。

21
00:01:22.880 --> 00:01:24.030
It's amazing.
会有很惊人的效果。

22
00:01:24.858 --> 00:01:26.008
Look at this.
看看这个。

23
00:01:27.247 --> 00:01:29.302
Here we are in London,
我们在伦敦，

24
00:01:29.326 --> 00:01:33.935
at the top of the Shard of Glass.
在碎片大厦的顶端。

25
00:01:35.129 --> 00:01:38.784
This is a building we completed a few years ago.
这是我们几年前完成的一个项目。

26
00:01:38.808 --> 00:01:44.529
Those people are well-trained workers,
这些是受过培训的工人，

27
00:01:45.665 --> 00:01:49.783
and they are assembling the top piece of the tower.
在组装塔的最高层。

28
00:01:51.006 --> 00:01:55.870
Well, they look like rock climbers.
他们看起来就像是攀岩者。

29
00:01:55.894 --> 00:01:57.044
They are.
他们的确是。

30
00:01:57.395 --> 00:02:00.030
I mean, they are defying the force of gravity,
我的意思是， 他们在与重力做斗争，

31
00:02:00.054 --> 00:02:02.254
like building does, by the way.
就像建筑物那样。

32
00:02:03.427 --> 00:02:05.744
We got 30 of those people --
我们有30个这样的人——

33
00:02:05.768 --> 00:02:10.636
actually, on that site, we got more than 1,400 people,
事实上，施工现场有超过1400个人，

34
00:02:10.660 --> 00:02:14.322
coming from 60 different nationalities.
来自60个国家。

35
00:02:14.898 --> 00:02:17.913
You know, this is a miracle. It's a miracle.
这是个奇迹，很不可思议。

36
00:02:17.937 --> 00:02:21.190
To put together 1,400 people,
把1400个来自不同国家的人，

37
00:02:21.214 --> 00:02:24.294
coming from such different places, is a miracle.
组合在一起，简直是奇迹。

38
00:02:24.667 --> 00:02:26.416
Sites are miracles.
施工现场也很让人惊叹。

39
00:02:26.977 --> 00:02:28.243
This is another one.
这是另一个。

40
00:02:29.159 --> 00:02:30.615
Let's talk about construction.
我们来谈一谈施工。

41
00:02:30.639 --> 00:02:34.556
Adventure, it's adventure in real life,
冒险，这是真实生活中的冒险，

42
00:02:34.580 --> 00:02:36.532
not adventure in spirit.
不是精神上的。

43
00:02:37.031 --> 00:02:40.953
This guy there is a deepwater diver.
这个人是深水潜水员。

44
00:02:40.977 --> 00:02:45.064
From rock climbers to deepwater divers.
从攀岩者到深水潜水员。

45
00:02:45.088 --> 00:02:46.849
This is in Berlin.
这是柏林。

46
00:02:46.873 --> 00:02:49.786
After the fall of the Wall in '89,
在1989年柏林墙倒塌之后，

47
00:02:49.810 --> 00:02:53.913
we built this building, connecting East Berlin to West Berlin,
我们建了这个建筑， 连接了东柏林和西柏林，

48
00:02:53.937 --> 00:02:55.540
in Potsdamer Platz.
它位于波坦兹广场。

49
00:02:55.977 --> 00:03:00.997
We got on that project almost 5,000 people.
有近5000人参与了这个项目。

50
00:03:01.885 --> 00:03:03.616
Almost 5,000 people.
差不多五千人。

51
00:03:04.426 --> 00:03:07.679
And this is another site in Japan,
这是另一个在日本的施工现场，

52
00:03:08.521 --> 00:03:10.846
building the Kansai Airport.
位于关西机场。

53
00:03:10.870 --> 00:03:14.021
Again, all the rock climbers, Japanese ones.
所有的攀岩者都是日本人。

54
00:03:14.782 --> 00:03:17.623
You know, making buildings together
一起打造建筑物

55
00:03:17.647 --> 00:03:21.850
is the best way to create a sense of cooperation.
是建立合作的最好方式。

56
00:03:22.231 --> 00:03:25.051
The sense of pride -- pride is essential.
荣誉感，荣誉是核心。

57
00:03:25.937 --> 00:03:29.325
But, you know, construction, of course,
不过理所当然的，施工也是

58
00:03:30.453 --> 00:03:34.196
is one of the reasons why architecture is amazing.
为什么建筑学 令人惊叹的原因之一。

59
00:03:34.644 --> 00:03:38.843
But there is another one, that is maybe even more amazing.
还有另一个理由，甚至更加惊艳。

60
00:03:39.517 --> 00:03:42.135
Because architecture is the art
因为建筑学是艺术，

61
00:03:42.159 --> 00:03:47.707
of making shelter for communities,
给社会创造庇护所的艺术。

62
00:03:47.731 --> 00:03:49.513
not just for individuals --
并不为个人——

63
00:03:49.858 --> 00:03:53.240
communities and society at large.
它造福于整个社区和社会。

64
00:03:53.612 --> 00:03:55.612
And society is never the same.
社会群体的构成各不相同。

65
00:03:56.612 --> 00:03:58.429
The world keeps changing.
这世界一直在变化。

66
00:03:59.770 --> 00:04:02.970
And changes are difficult to swallow by people.
人们是很难理解这种改变的。

67
00:04:03.318 --> 00:04:07.470
And architecture is a mirror of those changes.
而建筑就是这些变迁的镜子。

68
00:04:07.834 --> 00:04:13.432
Architecture is the built expression of those changes.
建筑是这些变迁的表现。

69
00:04:14.167 --> 00:04:18.494
So, this is why it is so difficult,
所以，这就是为什么它复杂高深，

70
00:04:19.231 --> 00:04:23.656
because those changes create adventure.
因为这些改变创造了冒险。

71
00:04:24.334 --> 00:04:27.064
They create adventure, and architecture is adventure.
它们本身就是一次次冒险， 然后它们又创造了冒险。

72
00:04:27.088 --> 00:04:30.754
This is the Centre Georges Pompidou in Paris,
这是位于巴黎的乔治 · 蓬皮杜中心，

73
00:04:30.778 --> 00:04:31.953
a long time ago.
很多年前的图片。

74
00:04:32.279 --> 00:04:35.597
That was back in time, '77.
大概拍摄于1977年。

75
00:04:36.443 --> 00:04:40.990
This was a spaceship landing in the middle of Paris.
这是在巴黎的中心的一个太空船。

76
00:04:42.276 --> 00:04:47.149
Together with my friend in adventure, Richard Rogers,
我和我的朋友，理查德 · 罗杰斯，

77
00:04:47.173 --> 00:04:50.921
we were, at the time, young bad boys.
我们那时候还是不良少年。

78
00:04:50.945 --> 00:04:52.149
Young, bad boys.
年轻的混混。

79
00:04:52.173 --> 00:04:53.208
(Laughter)
（笑)

80
00:04:53.232 --> 00:04:57.998
It was really only a few years after May '68.
那是在1968年5月的几年后。

81
00:04:58.683 --> 00:05:01.897
So it was a rebellion, pure rebellion.
发生了暴动，纯粹的暴动。

82
00:05:01.921 --> 00:05:04.953
The idea was to make
其背后的动机是为了证明

83
00:05:05.508 --> 00:05:10.230
the proof that cultural buildings should not be intimidating.
文化建筑不应该令人生畏。

84
00:05:10.254 --> 00:05:13.826
They should create a sense of curiosity.
它们应该激发一种好奇心。

85
00:05:14.699 --> 00:05:17.460
This is the way to create a cultural place.
这是一种创建文化场所的方式。

86
00:05:17.484 --> 00:05:21.343
Curiosity is the beginning of a cultural attitude.
好奇心是文化态度的起源。

87
00:05:22.008 --> 00:05:25.542
And there's a piazza there, you can see that piazza.
这里有一个广场。

88
00:05:26.199 --> 00:05:31.413
And a piazza is the beginning of urban life.
广场是城市生活的开端。

89
00:05:31.437 --> 00:05:34.183
A piazza is the place where people meet.
广场是人们见面的地方。

90
00:05:34.207 --> 00:05:36.216
And they mix experience.
他们交流着彼此的经历，

91
00:05:37.643 --> 00:05:39.275
And they mix ages.
打破了年龄的界限。

92
00:05:40.635 --> 00:05:44.785
And, you know, in some way,
以某种方式，

93
00:05:44.809 --> 00:05:49.529
you create the essence of the city.
你创造了城市的精髓。

94
00:05:50.290 --> 00:05:55.885
And since then, we made, in the office, so many other places for people.
从那时起，我们 又设计了很多其他的建筑。

95
00:05:55.909 --> 00:05:58.904
Here, in Rome, is a concert hall.
这里是罗马的一个音乐会大厅。

96
00:06:00.020 --> 00:06:01.825
Another place for people.
另一个为大众服务的地方。

97
00:06:01.849 --> 00:06:06.434
This building inside is actually designed by the sound, you can see.
这个建筑内实际上 是根据声音设计的。

98
00:06:07.202 --> 00:06:08.968
It's flirting with sound.
声音在其中肆意徜徉。

99
00:06:09.674 --> 00:06:11.650
And this is the Kansai Airport,
这个是日本的

100
00:06:12.309 --> 00:06:13.459
in Japan.
关西机场。

101
00:06:14.196 --> 00:06:17.035
To make a building, sometimes you need to make an island,
为了打造一个建筑， 有时你不得不建一座岛，

102
00:06:17.059 --> 00:06:18.655
and we made the island.
于是我们就建了这么一座岛。

103
00:06:19.540 --> 00:06:22.462
The building is more than one mile long.
这个建筑物的长度有一英里多。

104
00:06:23.262 --> 00:06:26.916
It looks like an immense glider, landing on the ground.
它看起来像一个巨大的滑翔机， 降落在地面上。

105
00:06:27.762 --> 00:06:29.746
And this is in San Francisco.
这是旧金山。

106
00:06:29.770 --> 00:06:31.437
Another place for people.
另一个为服务大众的场所。

107
00:06:31.738 --> 00:06:35.027
This building is the California Academy of Sciences.
这是加州科学博物馆。

108
00:06:35.640 --> 00:06:38.405
And we planted on that roof --
我们在屋顶上种植了植物——

109
00:06:39.053 --> 00:06:45.380
thousands and thousands of plants that use the humidity of the air,
成千上万的植物吸收空气中的水分，

110
00:06:45.404 --> 00:06:48.768
instead of pumping water from the water table.
不需要从下方抽水浇灌。

111
00:06:49.086 --> 00:06:51.286
The roof is a living roof, actually.
这个屋顶事实上是有生命的。

112
00:06:51.310 --> 00:06:54.964
And this building was made Platinum LEED.
这个建筑是符合 LEED白金级认证标准的。

113
00:06:55.699 --> 00:06:58.072
The LEED is the system to measure, of course,
LEED是一个用来衡量

114
00:06:58.096 --> 00:07:00.509
the sustainability of a building.
建筑可持续性的系统。

115
00:07:00.842 --> 00:07:05.476
So this was also a place for people
所以这也是一个 为人类服务的地方，

116
00:07:05.500 --> 00:07:07.905
that will stay a long time.
将会持续运营很长时间。

117
00:07:07.929 --> 00:07:09.826
And this is actually New York.
这个是在纽约。

118
00:07:09.850 --> 00:07:12.230
This is the new Whitney,
这栋建筑是新惠特尼，

119
00:07:12.254 --> 00:07:15.933
in the Meatpacking District in New York.
在纽约的肉类加工区。

120
00:07:16.866 --> 00:07:19.831
Well, another flying vessel.
另一个飞船。

121
00:07:20.928 --> 00:07:22.595
Another place for people.
另一个人文场所。

122
00:07:23.627 --> 00:07:26.516
Here we are in Athens, the Niarchos Foundation.
现在我们看到的是雅典的 Niarchos基金会。

123
00:07:26.540 --> 00:07:28.437
It's a library,
这是一个图书馆。

124
00:07:28.461 --> 00:07:32.151
it's an open house, a concert hall
它是一个开放性建筑， 有一个音乐厅，

125
00:07:32.175 --> 00:07:34.066
and a big park.
和一个大公园。

126
00:07:34.090 --> 00:07:39.140
This building is also a Platinum LEED building.
这个也是白金级标准的建筑物。

127
00:07:40.106 --> 00:07:45.584
This building actually captures the sun's energy with that roof.
这个建筑通过屋顶 使用太阳能供电。

128
00:07:46.834 --> 00:07:52.592
But, you know, making a building a place for people is good.
打造以人为本的建筑物是件好事。

129
00:07:53.008 --> 00:07:56.854
Making libraries, making concert halls,
建造图书馆，演奏厅，

130
00:07:56.878 --> 00:08:00.019
making universities, making museums is good,
大学，博物馆都是很好的做法。

131
00:08:00.043 --> 00:08:04.203
because you create a place that's open, accessible.
因为你建造了开放， 让所有人都能受益的地方。

132
00:08:05.262 --> 00:08:08.304
You create a building for a better world, for sure.
毫无疑问，你建造房子是 为了让世界变得更好。

133
00:08:09.191 --> 00:08:13.662
But there is something else
但是还有另外一个方面，

134
00:08:13.686 --> 00:08:16.839
that makes architecture amazing, even more.
使建筑更加美好。

135
00:08:17.699 --> 00:08:20.207
And this is the fact that
存在这样一个事实，

136
00:08:20.231 --> 00:08:26.055
architecture doesn't just answer to need and necessity,
建筑学不只是为 需要和必要性服务，

137
00:08:26.079 --> 00:08:32.528
but also to desires -- yes, desires -- dreams, aspirations.
还有欲望——是的， 欲望——梦想，愿望。

138
00:08:33.084 --> 00:08:34.971
This is what architecture does.
这就是建筑学的作用。

139
00:08:34.995 --> 00:08:40.529
Even the most modest hut on earth
即使是世界上最小的房子，

140
00:08:40.553 --> 00:08:42.386
is not just a roof.
也不仅仅是为了遮风挡雨。

141
00:08:42.410 --> 00:08:43.631
It's more than a roof.
它的作用超过了一个屋顶。

142
00:08:43.655 --> 00:08:45.056
It's telling a story;
它在讲述一个故事；

143
00:08:45.080 --> 00:08:49.586
it's telling a story about the identity of the people living in that hut.
讲述了曾经住在 那小屋的人的故事。

144
00:08:50.247 --> 00:08:51.397
Individuals.
个人的故事。

145
00:08:51.929 --> 00:08:55.175
Architecture is the art of telling stories.
建筑学是讲述故事的艺术。

146
00:08:56.032 --> 00:08:57.365
Like this one.
就像这一个。

147
00:08:58.350 --> 00:09:00.738
In London: the Shard of Glass.
伦敦的碎片大厦。

148
00:09:00.762 --> 00:09:05.455
Well, this building is the tallest building in Western Europe.
这是西欧最高的建筑物。

149
00:09:05.833 --> 00:09:11.223
It goes up more than 300 meters in the air, to breathe fresh air.
它高300多米，在上面 可以呼吸到新鲜的空气。

150
00:09:11.247 --> 00:09:14.992
The facets of this building are inclined,
这座建筑的外观是倾斜的，

151
00:09:15.016 --> 00:09:19.222
and they reflect the sky of London, that is never the same.
外墙会反射伦敦的天空， 景象千变万化。

152
00:09:19.246 --> 00:09:22.423
After rain, everything becomes bluish.
下过雨后， 一切都变成偏蓝的颜色。

153
00:09:23.016 --> 00:09:26.253
In the sunny evening, everything is red.
在晴天的下午， 一切都变成红色。

154
00:09:27.397 --> 00:09:30.397
It's something that is difficult to explain.
这是一种难以言喻的感觉。

155
00:09:31.183 --> 00:09:33.916
It's what we call the soul of a building.
我们把它叫做建筑的灵魂。

156
00:09:35.469 --> 00:09:38.633
On this picture on the left, you have the Menil Collection,
这张图片的左侧是menil系列

157
00:09:38.657 --> 00:09:40.155
used a long time ago.
很久以前所采用的。

158
00:09:40.179 --> 00:09:41.650
It's a museum.
这是一个博物馆。

159
00:09:41.674 --> 00:09:44.317
On the right is the Harvard Art Museum.
在右边的是哈佛艺术博物馆。

160
00:09:44.341 --> 00:09:47.610
Both those two buildings flirt with light.
这两个建筑都能和光影巧妙地互动。

161
00:09:48.151 --> 00:09:53.810
Light is probably one of the most essential materials in architecture.
光线或许是建筑中 最原始的材料了。

162
00:09:54.609 --> 00:09:56.275
And this is in Amsterdam.
这个建筑位于阿姆斯特丹。

163
00:09:56.990 --> 00:09:59.456
This building is flirting with water.
楼体和水面交相辉映。

164
00:10:00.982 --> 00:10:04.141
And this is my office, on the sea.
这个是我的办公室，在海上。

165
00:10:05.067 --> 00:10:07.935
Well, this is flirting with work.
不过它是在和工作调情。

166
00:10:08.392 --> 00:10:10.813
Actually, we enjoy working there.
事实上，我们很享受在那里工作。

167
00:10:10.837 --> 00:10:16.333
And that cable car is the little cable car that goes up to there.
小缆车把我们带到那上面。

168
00:10:17.453 --> 00:10:20.120
That's "The New York Times" in New York.
这是纽约时报大厦，位于纽约。

169
00:10:20.660 --> 00:10:24.000
Well, this is playing with transparency.
透明结构无处不在。

170
00:10:24.024 --> 00:10:27.624
Again, the sense of light, the sense of transparency.
这个建筑再一次体现了 对光线和透明感的运用。

171
00:10:29.183 --> 00:10:32.128
On the left here, you have the Magic Lantern in Japan,
在左边的图片，是“魔术灯”玻璃外墙，

172
00:10:32.152 --> 00:10:34.175
in Ginza, in Tokyo.
在日本东京的银座。

173
00:10:34.973 --> 00:10:38.690
And in the center is a monastery in the forest.
中间的是一座森林里的寺院。

174
00:10:39.239 --> 00:10:43.728
This monastery is playing with the silence and the forest.
寺院，寂静，森林，三者和谐共处。

175
00:10:44.675 --> 00:10:47.000
And a museum, a science museum.
（这张图是）一座博物馆， 科学博物馆。

176
00:10:47.651 --> 00:10:49.462
This is about levitation.
主题是关于磁悬浮。

177
00:10:51.159 --> 00:10:54.611
And this is in the center of Paris,
这个建筑是巴黎的中心，

178
00:10:54.635 --> 00:10:56.730
in the belly of the whale.
在鲸鱼的肚子里。

179
00:10:56.754 --> 00:10:59.366
This is the Pathé Foundation in Paris.
这是法国的Pathé基金会。

180
00:11:00.998 --> 00:11:03.925
All those buildings have something in common:
这所有的建筑物都有一个共同点：

181
00:11:03.949 --> 00:11:10.739
it's that something is searching for desire, for dreams.
一种追求欲望， 追求梦想的感觉。

182
00:11:11.207 --> 00:11:12.357
And that's me.
那个人是我。

183
00:11:12.381 --> 00:11:13.532
(Laughter)
（笑）

184
00:11:13.556 --> 00:11:16.040
Well, it's me on my sailing boat.
在我的帆船上。

185
00:11:17.675 --> 00:11:19.206
Flirting with breeze.
和海风调情。

186
00:11:20.722 --> 00:11:25.677
Well, there's not a very good reason to show you this picture.
好吧我承认，这并不是 一个展示照片的好借口。

187
00:11:25.701 --> 00:11:28.635
(Laughter)
（笑）

188
00:11:28.659 --> 00:11:30.603
I'm trying, I'm trying.
我尽力了。

189
00:11:30.627 --> 00:11:35.278
You know, one thing is clear: I love sailing, for sure.
不过很明显， 我喜欢扬帆出海。

190
00:11:35.302 --> 00:11:38.369
I actually also love designing sailing boats.
我实际上也爱设计帆船。

191
00:11:39.334 --> 00:11:43.791
But I love sailing, because sailing is associated with slowness.
我喜欢帆船， 因为帆船和慢节奏有着联系，

192
00:11:44.516 --> 00:11:45.794
And ...
以及…

193
00:11:46.707 --> 00:11:47.956
and silence.
以及沉默。

194
00:11:48.754 --> 00:11:50.621
And the sense of suspension.
悬浮的感觉。

195
00:11:51.461 --> 00:11:54.230
And there is another thing that this picture says.
照片还告诉了我们另外一件事。

196
00:11:54.651 --> 00:11:56.707
It says that I'm Italian.
它揭露了我是意大利人。

197
00:11:56.731 --> 00:11:58.969
(Laughter)
（笑）

198
00:11:58.993 --> 00:12:02.365
Well, there is very little I can do about that.
这我可没办法。

199
00:12:02.389 --> 00:12:03.746
(Laughter)
（笑）

200
00:12:04.120 --> 00:12:06.929
I'm Italian, and I love beauty.
我是意大利人，我追求美感。

201
00:12:07.540 --> 00:12:08.690
I love beauty.
我对美感十分着迷。

202
00:12:09.469 --> 00:12:13.738
Well, let's go sailing, I want to take you sailing here,
我们可以乘船出发， 我想要带你们去

203
00:12:13.762 --> 00:12:15.057
to this place,
这个地方，

204
00:12:15.612 --> 00:12:18.266
in the middle of the Pacific Ocean.
在太平洋的中心。

205
00:12:19.976 --> 00:12:23.516
This is the Jean-Marie Tjibaou Center.
这是Jean-Marie Tjibaou中心，

206
00:12:23.540 --> 00:12:26.365
It's for the Kanaky ethnic group.
属于卡耐基民族。

207
00:12:26.389 --> 00:12:28.744
It's in Nouméa, New Caledonia.
位于新喀里多尼亚的努美阿。

208
00:12:29.719 --> 00:12:31.799
This place is for art.
这是一个为艺术所生的地方。

209
00:12:31.823 --> 00:12:33.245
Art and nature.
艺术和自然。

210
00:12:34.369 --> 00:12:38.854
And those buildings actually flirt with the wind,
这些建筑和微风，和信风

211
00:12:38.878 --> 00:12:40.457
with the trade winds.
彼此依恋。

212
00:12:41.049 --> 00:12:44.390
They have a sound, they have a voice, those buildings.
它们有声音，这些建筑会发声。

213
00:12:44.414 --> 00:12:47.358
I'm showing this because it's about beauty.
我展示这张图片， 是因为它关乎美。

214
00:12:47.668 --> 00:12:49.724
It's about pure beauty.
纯粹的美。

215
00:12:50.262 --> 00:12:53.349
And let's talk about beauty for a moment.
现在我们来讲一下美。

216
00:12:53.707 --> 00:12:57.143
Beauty is like the bird of paradise:
美就像是天堂鸟：

217
00:12:58.116 --> 00:13:01.826
the very moment you try to catch it, it flies away.
在一个瞬间你试图抓住它， 可是它却飞走了。

218
00:13:02.810 --> 00:13:04.519
Your arm is too short.
你的胳膊还不够长。

219
00:13:06.056 --> 00:13:10.146
But beauty is not a frivolous idea.
但是美并不是一个轻浮的想法。

220
00:13:10.969 --> 00:13:12.169
It's the opposite.
正相反。

221
00:13:13.104 --> 00:13:15.739
In my native language, that is Italian,
在我的母语，意大利语中，

222
00:13:15.763 --> 00:13:17.550
"beautiful" is "bello."
"美丽“ 是”Bello“。

223
00:13:18.996 --> 00:13:23.390
In Spanish, "beauty" is "belleza."
在西班牙语中， ”美丽“是”belleza "。

224
00:13:24.629 --> 00:13:28.346
In Greek, "beautiful" is "kalos."
在希腊语中，“美丽”是“kalos”。

225
00:13:30.034 --> 00:13:34.987
When you add "agathos," that means "beautiful and good."
当你加上“agathos"， 它的意思就是”美丽和美好"。

226
00:13:34.941 --> 00:13:39.887
In no one of those languages, "beautiful" just means "beautiful."
但是在这些语言中， 美丽的意思不仅仅是美丽。

227
00:13:39.821 --> 00:13:41.480
It also means "good."
同时也是美好的意思。

228
00:13:43.115 --> 00:13:47.024
Real beauty is when the invisible
真正的美是无形与有形的结合，

229
00:13:47.842 --> 00:13:51.803
joins the visible, coming on surface.
并呈现于事物的表面。

230
00:13:52.120 --> 00:13:56.816
And this doesn't apply only to art or nature.
这不仅是在艺术和自然中适用。

231
00:13:58.327 --> 00:14:03.701
This applies to science, human curiosity, solidarity --
同时也适用于科学， 人类的好奇心，团结心——

232
00:14:03.725 --> 00:14:07.095
that's the reason why you may say,
这也是为什么你可能会说，

233
00:14:07.119 --> 00:14:10.405
"This is a beautiful person,"
“这是个美丽的人”，

234
00:14:10.429 --> 00:14:12.225
"That's a beautiful mind."
“这是美丽的灵魂”。

235
00:14:13.303 --> 00:14:17.510
This, this is the beauty that can change people
这种美可以把一个人变成

236
00:14:17.534 --> 00:14:18.732
into better people,
更好的人，

237
00:14:18.756 --> 00:14:22.076
by switching a special light in their eyes.
改变他们眼中的亮光。

238
00:14:22.492 --> 00:14:25.207
And making buildings for this beauty
然后为这种美打造建筑，

239
00:14:25.231 --> 00:14:27.913
makes cities better places to live.
使城市成为更好的居住地。

240
00:14:28.683 --> 00:14:30.229
And better cities
更好的城市

241
00:14:31.016 --> 00:14:32.922
make better citizens.
会孕育出更好的居民。

242
00:14:34.064 --> 00:14:36.968
Well, this beauty --
这种美——

243
00:14:36.992 --> 00:14:39.571
this universal beauty, I should say --
这普适的美，我应该这么说——

244
00:14:40.834 --> 00:14:44.300
is one of the few things that can change the world.
是极少的可以 改变世界的事情之一。

245
00:14:45.905 --> 00:14:49.547
Believe me, this beauty will save the world.
相信我， 这种美将会拯救世界。

246
00:14:50.183 --> 00:14:53.381
One person at a time, but it will do it.
慢慢来， 但是终将会发生的。

247
00:14:55.222 --> 00:14:56.452
Thank you.
谢谢。

248
00:14:56.476 --> 00:15:02.031
(Applause)
（鼓掌）